      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/3555" title="Spring Integration 2.2.0.M1 is released">Spring Integration 2.2.0.M1 is released</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Oleg Zhurakousky on Thu, 2012-05-17 08:34        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_4 first last active"><a href="/taxonomy/term/4" rel="tag" title="News and announcements
" class="active">News and Announcements</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>We are pleased to announce the first milestone release of Spring Integration 2.2 stream - <a target="_blank" href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-integration/docs/2.2.0.M1/reference/htmlsingle/">Spring Integration 2.2.0.M1</a>.<br />
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.springsource.org/spring-integration">Spring Integration</a> provides an extension of the Spring programming model to support the well-known <a target="_blank" href="http://www.eaipatterns.com/">Enterprise Integration Patterns</a></p>
<p>Aside from the usual bug fixes this release brings quite a few new features and upgrades:</p>
<ul>
<li>Dependency upgrades such as Spring 3.1.0.RELEASE, Spring AMQP 1.1.0.RELEASE, Spring Data Mongo 1.1.0.M1, Spring Gemfire 1.1.1.RELEASE</li>
<li>JPA support</li>
<li>Initial support for graceful shutdown of integration context</li>
<li>Support for 'Publisher Confirms and Returns' based on new features of Spring AMQP</li>
<li>etc.</li>
</ul>
<p>This release also contains many improvements. You can see full release notes <a target="_blank" href="https://jira.springsource.org/secure/ReleaseNote.jspa?projectId=10121&amp;version=12343">here</a> </p>
<p>For more information about Spring Integration, refer to the project's <a target="_blank" href="http://www.springsource.org/spring-integration">home page</a></p>
  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
